---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="About — Harmattan">
  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-100 tracking-tight mb-6">
      About Harmattan
    </h1>

    <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none space-y-6 text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        <strong class="text-gray-100">Harmattan</strong> is an open-source air quality
        monitoring platform built for Ghana. Named after the dry, dusty trade wind
        that blows from the Sahara across West Africa each year, Harmattan brings
        visibility to the invisible — the air we breathe.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-100 mt-8">The Problem</h2>
      <p>
        Ghana faces growing air pollution challenges. Rapid urbanization in Accra
        and Kumasi, industrial emissions from the Tema port zone, vehicle exhaust,
        and seasonal harmattan dust combine to create air quality conditions that
        affect millions — yet monitoring infrastructure remains sparse.
      </p>
      <p>
        The WHO estimates that 28,000 deaths annually in Ghana are attributable
        to air pollution. Most citizens have no way to check the air quality in
        their neighborhood, let alone make informed decisions about outdoor
        activities.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-100 mt-8">Our Solution</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-2">
        <li>
          <strong class="text-harmattan-400">Real-time monitoring</strong> — Aggregating
          data from OpenAQ, WAQI, and community sensors to provide live AQI readings
          for major cities.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong class="text-harmattan-400">Health advisories</strong> — Context-specific
          guidance based on Ghana's climate patterns, including harmattan season alerts.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong class="text-harmattan-400">Community reporting</strong> — Enabling
          citizens to report visible pollution sources like waste burning, industrial
          emissions, and dust from construction.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong class="text-harmattan-400">Open data</strong> — All collected data
          is publicly accessible to support research, policy, and community action.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-100 mt-8">Technology</h2>
      <p>
        Built with Astro, React, and Tailwind CSS. Deployed on Cloudflare's edge
        network for fast access across Africa. Data sourced from the World Air
        Quality Index (WAQI) and OpenAQ open data platforms.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-100 mt-8">Tech Hub Africa Hackathon 2026</h2>
      <p>
        Harmattan is a submission to the
        <a href="https://dorahacks.io" class="text-harmattan-400 hover:text-harmattan-300 underline">Tech Hub Africa Hackathon 2026</a>
        Pollution Control track. Our goal is to demonstrate how accessible technology
        can empower communities to understand and address air pollution in Ghana.
      </p>

      <div class="border-t border-surface-700 pt-6 mt-8">
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">
          Open source. Built with care for Ghana.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
